title: Fifty-One Tales
creator: Lord Dunsany (Edward J. M. D. Plunkett)
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
description: Very brief, well-crafted stories, many having surprise endings, all steeped in the dye of myth and calling to every reader's neglected imagination. (Summary by Thomas Copeland) Narrated by Thomas Copeland For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org . Download M4B (51MB)
subject: imagination; myth; Irish; prose poems; adult fairy tales; modern antiques;librivox;audio
